<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-02T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-02T06:00:00-05:00" n="145" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002 Manchuria/144: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_GJC1" type="from">Grew</persName>) to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-02T20:00:00+09:00">July 2, 1932—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 2—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>181. Italian Ambassador received instructions this afternoon to make
                            representations concerning Dairen customs similar to those made <pb facs="0225" n="127" xml:id="pg_127"/> by <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LSF1">Lindley</persName>, <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_MCDd1">Martel</persName> and myself. He will
                            do it Monday.<note n="86" xml:id="d145fn86">July 4.</note></p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_GJC1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>